✅ Basic Docker Commands & Use Cases

Command	Use Case
docker run -d -p 8080:80 nginx	Run NGINX container in background and expose port 80 on localhost:8080
docker ps	List running containers
docker ps -a	List all containers (running + stopped)
docker images	Show all downloaded Docker images
docker pull ubuntu	Download the latest Ubuntu image from Docker Hub
docker build -t myapp .	Build an image from a Dockerfile in the current directory
docker exec -it container_id bash	Open terminal inside a running container (interactive bash shell)
docker stop container_id	Stop a running container
docker start container_id	Start a stopped container
docker restart container_id	Restart a running or stopped container
docker rm container_id	Remove a stopped container
docker rmi image_id	Remove an image
docker logs container_id	Show logs from a container
docker inspect container_id	View detailed configuration of a container
docker network ls	List all Docker networks
docker volume ls	List all Docker volumes
docker system prune	Clean up unused containers, networks, and dangling images
docker system prune -a --volumes	Aggressively clean unused images, containers, and volumes
docker login	Authenticate with Docker Hub
docker push myuser/myapp	Push your image to Docker Hub

🛠️ Docker Compose Commands
Command	Use Case
docker-compose up -d	Start services in background using docker-compose.yml
docker-compose down	Stop and remove containers, networks, volumes defined by Compose
docker-compose build	Build or rebuild services
docker-compose logs	View logs from all services
docker-compose ps	List status of Compose services
